      "message": "Yes. In my case I want to control when to call `mctp_control_handler`. So my application does the handling and falls back to `mctp_control_handler` as default.\n\nThis allows two things: delay the response to a different context (think of handling the messages on an I3C interrupt, I don\u0027t want the reply to be sent from such a context, so I enqueue them to be sent later) and handle cases not handled by `mctp_control_handler` first (for instance, `mctp_ctrl_get_version` only handles \"base\" and \"control\" types, independent of types added).",
